WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.680 --> 00:00:06.085
In 2004, in his State of the Union
address, President George W Bush

00:00:06.085 --> 00:00:11.780
made universal adoption of electronic
records a ten-year national goal.

00:00:11.780 --> 00:00:14.870
He tasked a new Office of
the National Coordinator for

00:00:14.870 --> 00:00:19.340
Health IT with achieving that goal.

00:00:19.340 --> 00:00:22.950
In 2009, the Obama administration's
Health Information Technology for

00:00:22.950 --> 00:00:27.920
Economic and Clinical Health High
Tech Act provided funding of

00:00:27.920 --> 00:00:32.549
from $20 to $30 billion, the exact
amount depends on adoption levels.

00:00:32.549 --> 00:00:35.970
To reimburse hospitals and
eligible providers for

00:00:35.970 --> 00:00:38.800
adopting an electronic
health record system.

00:00:38.800 --> 00:00:42.050
Providers are eligible based
on the amount of Medicare or

00:00:42.050 --> 00:00:43.600
Medicaid patients they manage.

